You glance curiously around. The movie hasn't started yet, but you're very interested in the other versions of you around the theater. 
There is a blond, sporty, buff version of you, that is flirting with two giggling female versions of you that are clinging to his letter jacket. 
There is an artsy, bespectacled version of you sitting in the back row, who's drawing something on a sketchpad.
There is a dark, mysterious version of you with goth makeup and stylish clothing sitting next to a pale, frail-looking version of you who is wearing cut up clothing, with bloodstains. 

You continue looking around the room. Some of the versions are close to the way you are now, but many are very different, of all ages, sexes, hair colors. There appears to be only one constant-your eyes. They are the same hazel green, in each person. 

The seats around you begin to fill. A matronly version of you, in a gorgeous gown eases herself next to you. "Come on children", She says, beckoning her five children, all versions of you at various ages, to fill the seats around you. So we get to watch our movie now?"
, the youngest says. "Yes, darling", the matronly version says, smiling warmly. "This one is supposed to be an exciting one!"
"I think it's supposed to be a comedy", one of the other versions says, taking the seat next to you.

How many times have you seen this one?", the other asks.
 "This will be my seventh", the one next to you says.
